This could be a bug in the Java/MQ library or a simple coding issue on your part.

You should only ever get Reason Code 2495 - MQRC_MODULE_NOT_FOUND when your client application is connecting in &quot;bindings mode&quot; but by your code above, you appear to be connecting to the queue manager in &quot;client mode&quot;. Which does appear to be correct.

Here are some of the problems I see with your code:

- MQEnvironment class is not thread-safe and should not be used. You should set the connection parameters in a Hashtable and pass it to the MQQueueManager class.

- You should never use any MQ object that begins with &#39;SYSTEM&#39; (i.e. SYSTEM.DEF.SVRCONN). Create your own channel for your application. i.e. APP.TEST.CHL or whatever you want to call it.

- You should have a catch clause for the MQException and then dump out the MQ Completion Code and Reason Code.

- The close method for the opened queue should be in the finally clause.

Here&#39;s my suggestion on what the code should look like:

